            <div class="box BoxText">
                <h1 class="BoxHeader">Safety and Health Policy Statement</h1>	
                    <p class="em0">Shermco is committed to provide a safe and healthful work environment 
                    for all our employees and others who may work or visit our facilities.</p>
                     
                    <p class="em0">We will provide the necessary resources to promote and effectively implement 
                    our Safety and Health Management Systems and will comply with applicable 
                    federal, state and local safety and health regulations. Shermco will do 
                    this by pursuing VPP Star status within the OSHA Voluntary Protection Program (VPP). </p>

                    <p class="em0">All employees are expected to cooperate fully by following proper procedures 
                    and by providing proactive participation in protecting themselves and their fellow workers.</p>

                    <p class="em0">Shermco will maintain open lines of communication with employees to request 
                    information, receive comments and assistance regarding safety and health. 
                    All suggestions will be taken seriously.</p>

                    <p class="em0">Reporting of Injuries: All on-the-job injuries shall be reported immediately 
                    to a manager or supervisor, regardless of the severity of the injury, in order 
                    to ensure employees receive the proper first aid care and that the accident is 
                    documented and investigated. </p>

                    <p class="em0">Guiding Principles: A safe and efficient operation is the only acceptable standard. </p>

                    <p class="em0">If it isn’t safe, don’t do it. </p>
            </div>        
